&lt;p&gt;A new vacancy has arisen for a 1 yr fixed term Band 5 tissue viability nurse within our small but dynamic and growing team. Full or part time hours are both an option. Internal applicants may be considered for secondment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently redesigning our service to a more locality based model. This is a new post to support this new way of working. Although we plan to work in localities we will still be a countywide-based service. We are looking for motivated and enthusiastic individuals who have a passion for tissue viability, delivering quality care and helping others to achieve the same.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Those considering the post will need to have had experience of caring for patients with a wide range of wounds and in the prevention of avoidable skin breakdown. With support you will be involved in both formal and informal teaching programs and should be prepared to be actively involved in a range of service improvement projects undertaken by the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ongoing training and personal development will be provided through a structured process of supervision and peer support and you will be buddied to a band 6 TVN.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Penny Rubio&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Lead Tissue Viability&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: penny.rubio@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07920233477&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lauren Corcoran on 07786190725 email: lauren.corcoran@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk or Julie Hewish on 07385417295 email: julie.hewish@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk if you would like to discuss the role further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, due to Covid-19 an informal visit is not an option however we are happy to talk by phone or on Teams if you wish.&lt;/p&gt;
